---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Cyber Psycho / Netrunner Build - Ultimate Guide";
const description = "Complete Cyberpunk 2077 build guide for the Cyber Psycho playstyle — cyberware, skills, perks, weapons, and combat rotation for maximum damage.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="build-guide">
    <h1>🌃 Cyber Psycho / Netrunner Build - Ultimate Guide</h1>

    <div class="build-overview">
      <h2>🧠 Build Concept</h2>
      <p>The <strong>Cyber Psycho</strong> build combines Netrunner hacking with aggressive cyberware-enhanced combat. You breach enemies' systems with quickhacks, then finish them with overwhelming firepower. This build excels at:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Burst damage:</strong> Delete enemies in seconds with hack + weapon combos</li>
        <li><strong>Crowd control:</strong> Mass breach multiple targets simultaneously</li>
        <li><strong>Survivability:</strong> High health pool and damage mitigation from cyberware</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>🎯 Playstyle:</strong> You're a hybrid fighter. Start fights with hacks to weaken enemies, then rush in with weapons. Don't stay at range — this build rewards aggression.
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="attributes">
      <h2>📊 Attribute Point Allocation</h2>
      <p>At level 50, you'll have 78 attribute points total (base 20 + 58 from leveling). Here's the optimal distribution:</p>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Points</th>
          <th>Priority</th>
          <th>Why</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Intelligence</strong></td>
          <td>20</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</td>
          <td>Unlocks all Netrunner perks, increases hack damage, RAM capacity</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cool</strong></td>
          <td>18</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐</td>
          <td>Crit damage, stealth damage, reduces hack upload time</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Body</strong></td>
          <td>16</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐</td>
          <td>Health, stamina, heavy weapon handling, cyberware capacity</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Reflexes</strong></td>
          <td>12</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐</td>
          <td>Evade chance, assault rifle handling, movement speed</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Technical Ability</strong></td>
          <td>12</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐</td>
          <td>Armor, cyberware capacity, tech weapon damage</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <strong>💡 Leveling Order:</strong> Prioritize <strong>Intelligence first</strong> (get it to 20 by level 30), then <strong>Cool</strong> for crit damage, then <strong>Body</strong> for survivability.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="perks">
      <h2>🎯 Essential Perks (Must-Have)</h2>

      <div class="perk-category">
        <h3>Intelligence Tree (Netrunner)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>⚡ RAM Recovery (Tier 1):</strong> +0.25 RAM/sec. Essential for sustained hacking.</li>
          <li><strong>⚡ Quickhack Upload (Tier 2):</strong> Reduces upload time by 30%. Critical for burst damage.</li>
          <li><strong>⚡ Combat Hacking (Tier 3):</strong> Allows you to upload hacks while moving. Non-negotiable.</li>
          <li><strong>⚡ Memory Boost (Tier 4):</strong> +4 max RAM slots. Lets you chain more hacks.</li>
          <li><strong>⚡ Hack Queue (Tier 5):</strong> Upload 2 quickhacks simultaneously. Game-changing for multi-target fights.</li>
          <li><strong>⚡ Data Transfer (Tier 5):</strong> Killing an enemy with a hack refunds 2 RAM. Keeps you in the fight longer.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="perk-category">
        <h3>Cool Tree (Assassin)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>🎯 Precise Shot (Tier 1):</strong> +15% crit damage with all weapons.</li>
          <li><strong>🎯 Silent and Deadly (Tier 2):</strong> +20% crit chance after dodging. Synergizes with aggressive play.</li>
          <li><strong>🎯 Deep Pockets (Tier 3):</strong> Reduces cooldown on all abilities by 10%.</li>
          <li><strong>🎯 Cold Blood (Tier 4):</strong> +30% crit damage when health is above 80%. Rewards careful positioning.</li>
          <li><strong>🎯 True Eye (Tier 5):</strong> Headshots deal +50% damage. Essential for burst windows.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="perk-category">
        <h3>Body Tree (Tank)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>💪 Health Fork (Tier 1):</strong> +15% max health. Survivability.</li>
          <li><strong>💪 Comeback Kid (Tier 2):</strong> Heal 5% HP when using a health item. Extends fights.</li>
          <li><strong>💪 Pain Suppression (Tier 3):</strong> Take 10% less damage when health is below 50%. Clutch factor.</li>
          <li><strong>💪 Die Young (Tier 4):</strong> When health reaches 0, heal 30% instead of dying (1 charge per minute). Literal lifesaver.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cyberware">
      <h2>🦾 Cyberware Loadout</h2>
      <p>Cyberware is what makes this build tick. Here's the optimal setup:</p>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Slot</th>
          <th>Cyberware</th>
          <th>Effect</th>
          <th>Why It's Essential</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Operating System</strong></td>
          <td><strong>QHack (Tier 5)</strong></td>
          <td>+3 RAM slots, +50% quickhack damage, -30% upload time</td>
          <td>The core of the build. Without this, your hacks are too slow and weak.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Frontal Cortex</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Neocortex</strong></td>
          <td>+2 quickhack slots, +30% RAM regeneration</td>
          <td>Lets you upload more hacks in succession. Synergizes with Hack Queue perk.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Hands</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Mantis Blades</strong></td>
          <td>Melee weapon, can climb walls</td>
          <td>Close-range damage when hacks are on cooldown. Also utility for traversal.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Arms</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Gorilla Arms</strong></td>
          <td>+30% melee damage, can force open doors</td>
          <td>Backup damage and utility. Great for when you run out of RAM.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Legs</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Reinforced Tendons</strong></td>
          <td>Double jump</td>
          <td>Mobility. Lets you reposition quickly and reach high ground for better angles.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Nervous System</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Chronedistillators</strong></td>
          <td>Slows time by 70% for 16 seconds (2-minute cooldown)</td>
          <td>Burst window. Activate during tough fights to land multiple hacks instantly.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Integumentary System</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Subdermal Armor</strong></td>
          <td>+20% damage resistance</td>
          <td>Survivability. You'll be in the thick of combat, so you need the tankiness.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Skeletal System</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Reinforced Ankles</strong></td>
          <td>+20% fall damage reduction, +10% movement speed</td>
          <td>Mobility and safety. Lets you jump off buildings without penalty.</td>
        </tr>
      </table>

      <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>⚠️ Cyberware Capacity:</strong> This loadout requires 42 capacity. At level 50 with 16 Body + 12 Technical Ability, you'll have exactly enough. Don't over-invest in other cyberware or you won't fit everything.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="weapons">
      <h2>🔫 Weapon Loadout</h2>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>Primary: Iconic Smart Pistol "Nue"</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Type:</strong> Smart Pistol (auto-targeting)</li>
          <li><strong>Why:</strong> Bullets track enemies, so you can focus on hacking while the gun handles damage. Smart weapons also benefit from Intelligence scaling.</li>
          <li><strong>Mods:</strong>
            <ul>
              <li>+25% smart weapon damage</li>
              <li>+15% crit chance</li>
              <li>+30% headshot damage</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>Secondary: Iconic Tech Shotgun "Tactician"</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Type:</strong> Tech Shotgun (charges through walls)</li>
          <li><strong>Why:</strong> Burst damage for tough enemies. Charges through cover, so you don't have to expose yourself.</li>
          <li><strong>Mods:</strong>
            <ul>
              <li>+40% tech weapon damage</li>
              <li>+20% charge speed</li>
              <li>+15% crit damage</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="weapon-card">
        <h3>Melee: Mantis Blades (from Cyberware)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Type:</strong> Bladed melee weapon</li>
          <li><strong>Why:</strong> Fast attack speed, bleeds enemies, and scales with Reflexes. Great for finishing low-health targets.</li>
          <li><strong>Mods:</strong>
            <ul>
              <li>+30% bleed chance</li>
              <li>+25% attack speed</li>
              <li>+20% crit chance</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rotation">
      <h2>⚔️ Combat Rotation (How to Fight)</h2>
      <p>Here's the optimal sequence for maximum damage:</p>

      <div class="rotation-step">
        <h3>Phase 1: Opening (First 3 Seconds)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Activate Chronedistillators</strong> (slow time).</li>
          <li><strong>Upload "Contagion"</strong> quickhack to the nearest enemy. This spreads to nearby targets.</li>
          <li><strong>Upload "Mass Reboot"</strong> if facing 3+ enemies. This overheats their cyberware.</li>
          <li><strong>Upload "Cyberware Malfunction"</strong> to a high-priority target (boss or elite).</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="tip-box">
          <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> With Hack Queue perk, you can upload 2 hacks simultaneously. Prioritize Contagion + Cyberware Malfunction.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rotation-step">
        <h3>Phase 2: Burst Damage (Seconds 3-8)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Switch to Nue (Smart Pistol)</strong> and start shooting. The smart targeting handles aim while you focus on movement.</li>
          <li><strong>Keep moving.</strong> Use Reinforced Tendons to double-jump and reposition. Don't stand still.</li>
          <li><strong>Upload "Memory Wipe"</strong> to enemies that are isolated (not in groups). This stuns them for 5 seconds.</li>
          <li><strong>Headshot priority.</strong> With True Eye perk, headshots deal +50% damage. Aim for the head.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="rotation-step">
        <h3>Phase 3: Close Quarters (If Enemies Get Close)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Switch to Mantis Blades</strong> when enemies are within 5 meters.</li>
          <li><strong>Use "Blade" quickhack</strong> to summon a cyber-blade that deals massive damage to a single target.</li>
          <li><strong>Dodge-roll away</strong> if you're surrounded, then re-engage with the Tactician shotgun.</li>
          <li><strong>Activate "Comeback Kid"</strong> (health item) if your HP drops below 30%.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="rotation-step">
        <h3>Phase 4: Finish (When Enemies Are Low)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Upload "Suicide"</strong> quickhack to enemies below 20% HP. This instantly kills them and refunds 2 RAM (from Data Transfer perk).</li>
          <li><strong>Switch to Tactician shotgun</strong> for any remaining targets. One charged shot = one kill.</li>
          <li><strong>Reposition and reset.</strong> Wait for RAM to recharge before engaging the next group.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pros-cons">
      <h2>⚖️ Build Analysis</h2>

      <div class="pros-cons-grid">
        <div class="pros">
          <h3>✅ Strengths</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Extreme burst damage.</strong> Can delete bosses in under 10 seconds with proper rotation.</li>
            <li><strong>Versatile.</strong> Effective at all ranges — hacks for distance, smart gun for mid-range, mantis blades for close combat.</li>
            <li><strong>High survivability.</strong> Subdermal armor + Die Young perk = very hard to kill.</li>
            <li><strong>Crowd control.</strong> Contagion + Mass Reboot can disable entire rooms of enemies.</li>
            <li><strong>Fun factor.</strong> Feels like a true cyberpunk hacker-assassin hybrid.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cons">
          <h3>❌ Weaknesses</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>RAM-dependent.</strong> If you run out of RAM and hacks are on cooldown, you're just a guy with a gun.</li>
            <li><strong>Expensive.</strong> This build requires a lot of cyberware, which costs a fortune. Farm credits early.</li>
            <li><strong>Complex rotation.</strong> Takes practice to execute the hack → weapon → cyberware flow smoothly.</li>
            <li><strong>Weak to EMP.</strong> Enemies with EMP weapons can disable your cyberware temporarily. Avoid these fights or kill them first.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="leveling">
      <h2>📈 Leveling Path (1-50)</h2>
      <p>Here's how to progress efficiently:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Level 1-10:</strong> Focus on Intelligence perks. Get RAM Recovery and Quickhack Upload first.</li>
        <li><strong>Level 10-20:</strong> Pick up Combat Hacking and start using quickhacks aggressively in fights.</li>
        <li><strong>Level 20-30:</strong> Max out Intelligence (20 points). Unlock Memory Boost and Hack Queue.</li>
        <li><strong>Level 30-40:</strong> Invest in Cool for crit damage. Pick up Precise Shot and Silent and Deadly.</li>
        <li><strong>Level 40-50:</strong> Invest in Body for survivability. Get Health Fork, Pain Suppression, and Die Young.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <div class="call-to-action">
      <h2>🏆 Final Thoughts</h2>
      <p>The Cyber Psycho build is one of the most satisfying playstyles in Cyberpunk 2077. You're not just shooting — you're hacking, breaching, and overwhelming enemies with a combination of tech and skill. Master the rotation, manage your RAM, and you'll become the most dangerous merc in Night City.</p>
      <p><strong>Good luck, choom.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .build-guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .build-overview {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .info-box {
    background: #d1ecf1;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #17a2b8;
  }

  .tip-box {
    background: #d4edda;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .warning-box {
    background: #fff3cd;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
  }

  .perk-category {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #fcee09;
  }

  .perk-category ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .perk-category li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .perk-category li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .weapon-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #fcee09;
  }

  .rotation-step {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
  }

  .rotation-step h3 {
    color: #dc3545;
    border: none;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .pros-cons-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .pros, .cons {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .pros {
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .cons {
    border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
  }

  .call-to-action {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .call-to-action h2 {
    color: #fcee09;
    border: none;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pros-cons-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
